cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the application of deep learning models in various domains, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on improving learning with sparse and noisy samples and leveraging human advice/knowledge for better learning suggests that it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of deep models in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) is also mentioned, making these sub-categories likely as well. Finally, the use of human advice/knowledge in AI (cs.AI) and the potential for improving learning efficiency (cs.NE) are also relevant sub-categories.
